  "body": "In order to communicate and setup the fork id on the Consensus Layer network, we use SSZ encoding.\r\n\r\nWhat is needed is to write all the Resp/Req data structs defined in https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#the-reqresp-domain (scroll down in the specs to see them), and then implement SSZ encoding for all of them (this quite easy as you can use  https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/fastssz to generate the szz encodings). The first thing that would be very needed is an equivalent of https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/211c5c2c5c5760a7f8966db26262d78853d0b388/proto/prysm/v1alpha1/p2p_messages.pb.go#L170. NOTE: NextForkEpoch is just a uint64 under an alias, and you can just ignore the first 3 fields, the file is an autogenerated protobuf anyway.",
